The paper deals with the problem of detecting hidden cameras through analyzing video data transmitted by potentially hidden cameras. This involves computer vision techniques such as similarity measures and neural networks, which are commonly used in the computer vision field (cs.CV). The paper also addresses security and privacy concerns related to hidden cameras, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques such as neural networks, which are commonly used in the machine learning field (cs.MM, cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with wireless communication and network security, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
